721129f-a.title: Manhattan: Liberty Street - Greenwich Street
721129f-a.text:
Liberty Strect, north side, between Creenwich and
washington Streets, showing a 9 foot alley between No's 129 and
131 which according to the City Record appears to be ownerless.
Its is 72 feet deep and of irregular wicth, leading to the rear of
buildings tnat face on tne west side of Sreenwich Street. At
the northern extremity is the side of thne building in which John
Thomas Smith lived and recently died in; No. 154 Greenwich Street.
August 1938
George D. Chinn
NO REP.UDU21IONS7
